Inform the relevant field with the amount of franking credits attached to assessable distributions received from Australian corporate tax entities. Do not include franking credits attached to a distribution that is exempt income or non-assessable non-exempt income, franked distributions received from a New Zealand franking company (include these at Information statement- Reconciliation to taxable income or loss- Australian franking credits from a New Zealand company), or - a distribution where the shares are not held at risk as required under the holding period and related payments rules, or there is other manipulation of the imputation system. There is no entitlement to a franking tax offset. For most companies, the amount of franking credits included in this field is allowable as a tax offset and should be claimed at 'Rebates/tax offsets' in the Calculation statement. If the company is a life insurance company or organisation entitled to claim a refund of excess franking credits, inform the relevant field with the refundable amount at 'Other refundable credits' in the Calculation statement.
Amount paid by company to investor - Franking credit
